cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as word sense induction (WSI) and clustering of word usages within a sentence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses pre-trained RNN language models (ELMo) and BERT, which are machine learning models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for interpreting the resulting clusters, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also performs extensive error analysis, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
